cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper proposes an extension of the fully recursive perceptron network (FRPN) model for vectorial inputs to include deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs). This falls under the domain of neural computing and hence, cs.NE is the most likely category.
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The proposed method is evaluated on several image classification benchmarks, which falls under the domain of computer vision. Hence, cs.CV is also a likely category.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a new architecture for deep learning and evaluates it on image classification tasks. This falls under the domain of machine learning and hence, cs.LG is also a likely category.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a new architecture for deep learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. Hence, cs.AI is also a likely category.
5. cs.SD (Sound) - There is no mention of sound or audio in the paper, but it is possible that the proposed architecture could be applied to sound or audio data. Hence, cs.SD is a less likely category.
